<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-136-342 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 799 410</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Week  June 3 1991 v8 n22 p46(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>InfoLAN links LANs to Infonet global network. (local area networkto wide area network connectivity management service)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Zimmerman, Michael R.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Infonet Services Corp. (Communication systems).andO;Topic:     Local Area NetworksWide Area NetworksNetwork ManagementTelecommunications ServicesInternetworking.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>By Michael R. ZimmermanandM;Global network service provider Infonet recently announced its firstLAN-to-WAN connectivity management service.andM;Called InfoLAN, the service lets organizations link multiple andgeographically dispersed LANs over Infonet's global network.andP;  Infonet willinstall and manage the hardware necessary to implement InfoLAN, which runs onTCP/IP and Source Route Bridging communications protocols, said Infonetofficials in El Segundo, Calif.andM;&quot;InfoLAN solves the internetworking problem of connectivity and speed at theapplication level rather than the technology level,&quot; said Jennifer Pigg,senior industry analyst of data communications at The Yankee Group Inc., amarket-research firm in Boston.andM;InfoLAN enables throughput rates between 9.6K bps and T-1 speeds of 1.44Mbps, said Jean-Noel Moneton, vice president of Infonet's communicationservices.andP;  InfoLAN, available now, works with Cisco Systems Inc.'s routersand NetCentral Station network-management software, which is based on theSimple Network Management Protocol for managing hardware devices across thenetwork.andP;  Management reports are sent electronically to the customer daily,weekly and monthly.andM;Future versions of the service will be compatible with routers from WellfleetCommunications Corp. and Proteon Inc., said Moneton.andP;  Infonet also plans toadd support for DECnet, IPX and AppleTalk communications protocols early nextyear, he said.andM;The 21-year-old Infonet controls 37 percent of the internationaldata-transport market, according to the Yankee Group.andM;Pricing for InfoLAN varies, but it will include a flat, monthly access fee.andO;Infonet can be reached at (213) 335-2600.andO;</TEXT></DOC>